charges.charge_disposition: RESENTENCED: Count 1: Custody U.S. Bureau of Prisons for a period of THREE (3) MONTHS, with no period of supervised release to follow. All elements of the Judgment and Order of May 26, 1995, except the term of probation, will remain a part of the sentence. The defendant shall report to the U.S. Attorney's Office in the district in which he is released within 72 hours of release from the custody of the Bureau of Prisons and shall remain in contact with the U.S. Attorney's Office until the balance left owing on any fine and/or assessment is paid in full. (1)
